<p>i love wikipedia.</p>

<p>but i have felt that my contributions
&#8212; on topics where i do have expertise &#8212;
have been warped by people who merely want
to &#8220;make it sound like an encyclopedia&#8221;
without having any knowledge of the topic.</p>

<p>it seems to me that the experts that
wikipedia so desperately needs will be
<em>precisely</em> those people who are <em>not</em>
making edits to a large number of topics.</p>

<p>-bowerbird</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.performancepoetry.com">bowerbird</a>
